Secret U.S. tests of Agent Orange in Panama during the Vietnam War may have exposed many residents and military personnel to potentially lethal chemicals, The Dallas Morning News reported today.
Today's report, which compared the health of exposed veterans with 1,300 other Vietnam veterans who had no contact with Agent Orange, said that as dioxin levels in the body increased, the presence and severity of adult diabetes increased.
